<plot>Considered by many to be CBS' answer to the "Cosby Show", Charlie &amp; Co. followed the Richmond family, headed by dad Charlie, played by funny-man Flip Wilson a blue-collar worker and his wife, Diana, played by Gladys Knight. Though it was seen as more realistic and relateable than the upscale Huxtable family, Charlie &amp; Co. was not able to latch on to the public the way Cosby had.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?100258</url></doc>
